Transcription.Text: The colonial Secretary, Mr. Lennox Boyd, allowed the storm to beat around him. The situation remained unchanged; Dr. Banda and his colleagues remained in prison. A considerable section of British opinion, aware at last of the great potentialities for danger in Central Africa, began to view the whole Federation with deep uneasiness.
